<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Practice One</title>
</head>
<body>
    <!--there are two types of markup
     1. structural markup
     2. semantic markup-->


     <!--STRUCTURAL MARKUP-->
    <!--headings from 1 to 6 -->
    <h1>Heading h1</h1>
    <h2>Heading h2</h2>
    <h3>Heading h3</h3>
    <h4>Heading h4</h4>
    <h5>Heading h5</h5>
    <h6>Heading h6</h6>

    <!--paragraph tag-->
    <p>this is inside paragraph tag, each paragraph starts with new line</p>
    <!--we can use bold tag with or without paragraph tag-->
    This is how we make a word appear <b>bold  </b>
    <!--we can use italic tag with or without paragraph tag-->
   This is how we make a word appear <i>italic</i>

   <!--super and sun script tags-->
   <p>On the 4<sup>th</sup> of September you will learn
    about E=MC<sup>2</sup>.</p>
    <p>The amount of CO<sub>2</sub> in the atmosphere
    grew by 2ppm in 2009<sub>1</sub>.</p>

    <!-- when a browser indentifies 2 or more white space at same place
    , it reduces that space to one. this concept is known as white space collapsing-->


    <!-- to start in a new line we use br (line break) tag forward slash can come after and before too-->
    <p>hi my name is abc .<br />i am learning html5 from basic.</p>

    <!--to draw a horizontal line we use hr (horizontal rule) tag  forward slash can come after and before too-->
    <p>hiiii<hr />byeeee</p>


    <!-- there are tags where we write no text in between, these are known as empty elements.
    it is a great way to write these  a space after the tag and before the slash--> 
     <p>Venus is the only planet that rotates clockwise.</p>
     <hr />
     <p>Jupiter is bigger than all the other planets combined.</p>

     <!--SEMANTIC MARKUP-->
     the tag <em>emphasis</em> is used. makes text italic  
     the tag<strong> strong</strong> is used. makes text bold
     the tag<blockquote> blockquote </blockquote> is used. 
     the tag<q>q (quote) </q>is used. 
     <!--in html 4 , there were two tags for specified type( <abbr> & <acronym>), but in html5 there is just one tag <abbr> for both-->
     <p><abbr title="Professor">Prof</abbr> Stephen Hawking is a theoretical physicist and cosmologist.</p>
    <p><abbr title="National Aeronautics and Space Administration">NASA</abbr> do some crazy space stuff.</p>

    <!-- cite  should not be used in html5 as much and definations -->
    <p>this is from <cite>the BOOK</cite>. it makes text italic</p>
    
</body>    

